Like you said,we don't have time for this.

321
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:43,177
好了,谢谢你
Great,thank you.

322
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:49,857
哪里也别想去,啊?
Weren't planning on going anywhere,were you?

323
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:52,454
不,我从来没有过这个想法
No,the thought hadn't even crossed my mind.

324
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:55,578
有没有认跟你说过你有点妄想症?
Has anyone ever told you you're paranoid?

325
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:58,128
有,我还要你的电话
Yep,I will take your phones,too...

326
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:01,531
以防你们在我背后搞小动作
just in case you were tempted to make any arrangements behind my back.

327
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:03,415
我会给你的,但我的意思是说
I would give it,but I mean,

328
00:24:03,416 --> 00:24:05,852
我奶奶说过今天要打电话给我,她非常孤单
me Nan said she might call today.She gets very Ionely.

329
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:14,815
哦,如果奶奶打来了
Yeah,if me Nan calls...

330
00:24:15,540 --> 00:24:18,418
就跟她说明天我会去看她
just tell her I'll come and see her tomorrow.

331
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:21,855
你拿到你要的东西了吗?
Did you get what you needed?

332
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:25,613
画还在,Danny
It's still there,Danny.

333
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:34,656
那么,你男朋友是不是在这里工作?
So,your boyfriend work round here,does he?

334
00:25:37,020 --> 00:25:39,580
你有没有男朋友?没有?
You got a boyfriend?No?

335
00:25:40,780 --> 00:25:42,498
怎么,你脾气不好?
What,you're more of a cat person?

336
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:51,130
嘿,停下里
Hey,stop them !

337
00:25:51,220 --> 00:25:53,051
把我们的包还给我们,小偷!
Give our bag back,pricks!

338
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:55,895
嘿,停车!
Hey,stop that car!

339
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:00,095
这下好了
Great.

340
00:26:00,180 --> 00:26:02,375
- 你怎么追的啊? - 好啊,我就是这么追的
- You call that running? - Yes,I call that running.

341
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:04,610
- 那你去哪里了? - 就在你后面
- Where were you? - Right behind you.

342
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:07,612
- 如果我知道你会减速 - 听着,这是我的错
- lf I knew you were going to slow down... - Look,it's not my fault.

343
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:09,656
- 这可不是我的错 - 当然是你的错
- Do not make this my fault. - It is your fault!

344
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:11,776
你让个白痴拿了箱子 这还我的错?
You let some idiot take the case and it's my fault?

345
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:13,498
- 闭嘴! - 我是跟着你过来的
- Shut up! - I've had it up to here with you.

346
00:26:13,580 --> 00:26:16,333
- 你老是自做主张 - 我们现在去把它找出来
- Always got to have things your own way. - Let's sort it out now!

347
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:17,978
闭嘴,Danny,上车!
Shut up,Danny,and get in the car!

348
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:24,577
哦,这算什么意思?
Is that supposed to mean something?

349
00:26:24,660 --> 00:26:27,538
我们刚刚搞砸了,好吗?那是真品
We just got screwed,all right?That was the real artwork.

350
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:31,973
我们真的要这么千方百计 要我打电话给拍卖行
Do we really have to go through the whole me phoning the auction house...

351
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:35,416
让我在最后一刻制止我?我想如果你们想的话,我可以这么做
you stopping me at the last minute thing?I mean,we can if you like.

352
00:26:38,660 --> 00:26:39,809
跟你说吧,她不会这么做的
Told you she wouldn't go for it.

353
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:42,289
我想你没有更好的主意了
I didn't see you coming up with any better ideas.

354
00:26:42,380 --> 00:26:44,211
你到底怎么做到的?
When exactly did you arrange it?

355
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:47,098
我去看邮件的时候 在旅馆留了张便条给Ash
I left a note for Ash at the hotel,when I checked my mail.

356
00:26:48,460 --> 00:26:49,939
你不能因此怪我们吧?
You can't blame us for trying,can you?

357
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:54,013
哦,好吧,如果你们不这么急着摆脱我 我想我也不会这么急
Yeah,well,I'd probably be more worried if you weren't trying to ditch me,I suppose.

358
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:55,499
换给你
Here you go.

359
00:26:57,020 --> 00:26:58,533
他把艺术品拿哪里了?
Where's he taking the artwork?

360
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:05,936
你真的以为我们不知道?
Did you really think we wouldn't find out?

361
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:09,569
什么?你很抱歉?哦,这太迟了,不是吗?
What's that?You're sorry?Well it's too late,son,isn't it?

362
00:27:13,620 --> 00:27:15,019
她买了没有?
Did she buy it?

363
00:27:19,860 --> 00:27:21,054
放了他
Let him go.

364
00:27:22,780 --> 00:27:25,453
我说了,放他走
I said,let him go.

365
00:27:29,980 --> 00:27:32,414
Mickey,我很抱歉 是她威胁我
Mickey,I'm sorry.She was trying to blackmail me.

366
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:36,417
她弄了假钞 她说我会进监狱
She planted some counterfeit money.She told me I was going to prison.

367
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:38,934
当我们来跟你算帐的时候 你会希望如此的
You'll wish you had when we get through with you.

368
00:27:39,460 --> 00:27:42,020
Mickey,求求你.我们认识多久了?
Mickey,please.How long have we known each other?

369
00:27:42,340 --> 00:27:43,932
我别无选择
I didn't have any choice.

370
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:46,529
Danny?
Danny?

371
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:49,533
上帝,Eddie,你让我有揍你的冲动
Jesus,Eddie,you're making me want to kick you.

372
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:53,295
我想我们还要去拍卖会
I believe we have an auction to go to.

373
00:27:54,460 --> 00:27:55,893
他怎么办?
What about him?

374
00:27:57,620 --> 00:28:00,976
我拿到我的钱,这就是你的事
What you do after I get my money,that's your business.

375
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:02,614
我们有过协议
We had a deal.

376
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:07,019
- 你不能这样! - 待会见,Eddie.
- You can't do this! - Later,Eddie.

377
00:28:21,780 --> 00:28:23,099
我不小心滑了下
I slipped.

378
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:35,977
- 一点历史 - 它在哪儿?
- A slice of history. - And where is it?

379
00:28:36,460 --> 00:28:38,655
今天下午晚点会到
It's not arriving till later this afternoon.

380
00:28:39,180 --> 00:28:41,648
我已经迫不及待要看一眼了
I didn't expect to get another shot at it so soon.

381
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:44,857
- 你料到这么多的竞争了吗? - 都是些怪人
- Are you expecting much competition? - Only the geek.

382
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:48,530
Neil Davis.连环画收藏家
Neil Davis.Comic book collector.

383
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:51,089
纯粹是处于角色的神秘
Thinks it's all about the mythology of the characters.

384
00:28:51,180 --> 00:28:53,614
与艺术意义完全无关
No appreciation of the artistic significance.

385
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:56,089
我想他甚至与无法拼出Lichtenstein
I mean he couldn't even spell Lichtenstein.

386
00:28:57,740 --> 00:29:01,449
那一旦他得到了这么件真品 那将是巨大的悲哀
Then it would be a tragedy if he acquired such an important piece.

387
00:29:01,780 --> 00:29:04,055
我会确保他不会得逞
I will just have to make sure that he doesn't.

388
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:13,052
嗨,你来了
Hi.You made it.

389
00:29:14,020 --> 00:29:15,009
给你
Here.

390
00:29:15,860 --> 00:29:18,852
- 你没必要这样 - 哦,我心甘情愿
- You didn't have to do that. - Yeah,I wanted to.

391
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:21,458
这位是谁啊?
And who's this?

392
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:25,889
这是鸟?飞机?不,这是
Is it a bird?Is it a plane?No,it's....

393
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:34,815
是Tim.跟Neil打个招呼,Tim
This is Tim.Say hello to Neil,Tim.

394
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:38,173
他非常喜欢自己的装扮 不肯脱下来
He absolutely loves his costume.Wouldn't take it off.

395
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,613
我希望我也有这么套行头
I wish I'd got one.

396
00:29:55,380 --> 00:29:57,336
也许下一次?
Maybe some other time?

397
00:29:59,300 --> 00:30:01,018
- 我们进去吧? - 好的
- Shall we go in? - Yeah.

398
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:04,090
他非常兴奋
He's really excited.

399
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:19,979
好吧,他要花些时间 那我们找个地方坐坐
Right,he'll be a while.So let's take the weight off.

400
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:26,489
那我们现在在看的是什么?
So,what is it we are looking at?

401
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:31,899
黑色风暴原版的封面,出品的第一版
The original artwork for the cover of Black Storm,Issue One,when it arrives.

402
00:30:35,660 --> 00:30:37,378
所以我可以把它当作是个大买卖?
And I take it this is a big deal?

403
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:38,535
是的
Yeah.

404
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:41,930
他是第一个真正意义上的超级英雄 有着巨大的影响力
He was one of the very first superheroes.Massively influential.

405
00:30:42,820 --> 00:30:44,970
为我们所知的后来的连环画建立了雏形
Shaped the future of comics as we know them.

406
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:47,859
- 噢,了不起  - 我打算竞拍它
- Wow. - I'm bidding for it.

407
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:54,532
那人是谁?
And who's that?

408
00:30:54,620 --> 00:30:57,657
Gideon Sturock,竞争对手
Gideon Sturock.The competition.

409
00:30:59,060 --> 00:31:01,449
看上去是个自命不凡的傻子
Looks like a pretentious little prat to me.

410
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:04,217
他自称是艺术收藏家
He calls himself an art collector.

411
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:07,574
他根本不顾画中的人物或神话
He doesn't care about the characters or the mythology.

412
00:31:08,540 --> 00:31:10,292
对他来说,这不过是又一个战利品
It's just another trophy to him.

413
00:31:11,860 --> 00:31:14,135
那我希望你别让他得逞
I hope you are not going to let him buy it,then?

414
00:31:14,220 --> 00:31:15,858
我会尽我所能的
Not if I can help it.

415
00:31:18,740 --> 00:31:21,208
- 那个怪人 - 真的吗?
- The geek. - Really?

416
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:25,049
跟他在一起的迷人女士是谁?
Who's that rather attractive young woman with him?

417
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:28,339
如果她和这么个没用的人在一起 大概是个妓女
If she's with a loser like that,probably a hooker.

418
00:31:34,060 --> 00:31:38,338
我非常期待看你打败他时 他脸上的表情
I'm very much going to enjoy seeing the look on his face when you outbid him.

419
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:44,819
干得好,Ash
Good work,Ash.

420
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:50,016
闭路电视搞定了,到我们了
CCTV's rigged.We're on.

421
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:56,618
你俩先走,行吧?
You two go ahead,all right?

422
00:31:57,300 --> 00:31:58,415
这有关系吗?
Is there a problem?

423
00:31:58,580 --> 00:32:02,493
你们将要犯罪 而显然,我不想被连累
You are about to commit a crime.Obviously I can't be associated with that.

424
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:03,849
好吧
Okay.

425
00:32:08,220 --> 00:32:11,610
你自己去喝杯茶,行吧 还有甜圈,怎么样?
Get yourself a nice a cup of tea,yeah?Sticky bun,all right?

426
00:32:14,820 --> 00:32:18,290
Danny,我就在你后面 现在,你别跟我说话
Danny,I will be right behind you.Now,you don't talk to me...

427
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:20,575
你不知道我 不认识我
you don't acknowledge me,you don't know me...

428
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:22,651
但你要在我的视野范围内 听清楚了没有?
but you stay in sight.Clear?

429
00:32:46,180 --> 00:32:50,173
几点开始,3:30?好的,行不行?
What time does it start,3:30?Okay,is that any good?

430
00:32:51,540 --> 00:32:52,734
叫Colossal
Colossal.

431
00:33:20,340 --> 00:33:22,854
- 他在那儿干吗? - 他妈我怎么会知道?
- What's he doing here? - How the hell am I supposed to know?

432
00:33:22,940 --> 00:33:25,329
- 怎么回事? - 计划大师搞砸了
- What is going on? - Master planner here screwed up.

433
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:26,899
拍卖行通常会有一个专家
The auction house usually have an expert...

434
00:33:26,980 --> 00:33:28,379
进来对艺术品进行鉴定
come in and authenticate the artwork...

435
00:33:28,460 --> 00:33:30,610
- 在进行拍卖之前 - 好,你知道的
- before they put it up for auction. - Yeah,you knew that.

436
00:33:30,700 --> 00:33:33,578
是,我是知道,但不是以前那个
Yes,I did,but this is not their usual guy.

437
00:33:33,660 --> 00:33:35,730
他们找来的这个6个月前 把我们哄了出去
The guy they've brought in rumbled us six months ago...

438
00:33:35,820 --> 00:33:37,538
我们想卖幅Andy Warhol画作的赝品
when we tried to sell a forged Andy Warhol print.

439
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:39,656
是的,我们拿着一大堆垃圾邮件
Yeah,we had these tins of Spam.

440
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:41,810
我们让他们忙坏了 他们很有意思
We'd had them all stacked up.They were cute.

441
00:33:41,900 --> 00:33:44,539
我们不能在他在场的情况 下拍卖这件艺术品
We cannot put the artwork up for auction with him there.

442
00:33:44,780 --> 00:33:46,452
我们必须要推迟
We are going to have to postpone.

443
00:33:46,820 --> 00:33:49,209
除了要我做出格的事情,这倒方便了
Just till I'm out of the way.Deeply convenient.

444
00:33:49,300 --> 00:33:51,575
你要不要我们走出去 向你证明这一切?
Would you like us to step outside and prove it to you?

445
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:53,139
好吧,那Ash怎么办?是的
All right,what about Ash?Yeah.

446
00:33:53,220 --> 00:33:55,495
我们可以让他先装下去,他能做到的
We will get him all,you know,disguised,he can do it.

447
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:57,730
不行,他已经为闭路电视服务过了
No,he's been servicing their CCTV.

448
00:33:58,860 --> 00:34:02,136
- 那我们要另外找人 - Danny,没有时间了,对不起
- We'll have to get someone else,then. - Danny,there is no time.Sorry.

449
00:34:02,220 --> 00:34:06,657
- 我是说放弃这个 - 不行,我们不可能再弄次闭路电视的
- I'm calling it off. - No,we can't rig the CCTV a second time.

450
00:34:06,740 --> 00:34:09,891
买家们已经准备好了,每个人都 各就各位了.我们必须上
Buyers are ready.Everybody's in place.Got to go now.

451
00:34:10,900 --> 00:34:14,290
- 我可以做 - 哦,是的,我可不这么想
- I could do it. - Yeah,right.I don't think so.

452
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:16,496
是的,她可以做么
Yeah.She can do it.

453
00:34:16,580 --> 00:34:18,411
然后看着她时候带着钱消失
And watch her disappear with the money afterwards.

454
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:19,569
你疯了?
Are you out of your mind?

455
00:34:19,660 --> 00:34:22,538
我们还换的是吧?我们还有原迹
We still make the switch.Yeah?We still got the original.

456
00:34:22,620 --> 00:34:24,576
我是说,那也能行
I mean,that could work.

457
00:34:26,780 --> 00:34:28,975
我想你该试着相信我
I guess you're gonna have to trust me.

458
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:43,208
好吧,拍卖会再等一位Henshaw先生
All right,the auction house are expecting a Mr.Henshaw.

459
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:46,895
我打电话告诉他们我的助理 代我来送艺术品
I'll call and tell them that my PA will be delivering the artwork instead of me.

460
00:34:46,980 --> 00:34:50,290
你换之前在大厅等我回来,没问题吧?
Wait until I am back in the foyer before you make the switch,all right?

461
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:52,940
当你上的时候,我可不想离你这么近
I don't want to be anywhere near you when you do it.

462
00:34:57,380 --> 00:34:58,972
Williams先生,请
Mr.Williams,please.

463
00:35:21,260 --> 00:35:24,218
嗨,我是Henshaw先生的助手
Hello,I'm Mr.Henshaw's PA.

464
00:35:25,180 --> 00:35:26,499
我想你在等我
I think you are expecting me.

465
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:34,929
那么,我得知你的专家今天不在吗?
So,I understand your own expert isn't in today?

466
00:35:35,020 --> 00:35:37,409
Paul?不,他今天早上打电话说病了
Paul?No,he called in sick this morning.

467
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:39,855
我们不得不最后时刻请来David
We had to get David in here at the last minute.

468
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:46,218
- 这是真品 - 今天展上最好的
- It's authentic. - Best get this on display.

469
00:35:48,340 --> 00:35:52,219
我知道Henshaw先生要赶飞机 所以我会开张银行汇款给你
I know Mr.Henshaw has a plane to catch,so I will issue you with a banker's draft...

470
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:55,292
- 一卖出就给你 - 好的,谢谢
- immediately after the sale. - Great.Thank you.

471
00:36:19,780 --> 00:36:22,738
我有感觉,你将非常失望
Something tells me you are going to be horribly disappointed.

472
00:36:23,380 --> 00:36:25,689
我们走着瞧,不是吗?
We'll just have to see about that,won't we?

473
00:36:26,260 --> 00:36:27,375
她真漂亮
Pretty girl.

474
00:36:30,620 --> 00:36:32,417
她开价多少?
How much does she charge?

475
00:36:33,260 --> 00:36:34,249
好了
Yeah.

476
00:36:38,580 --> 00:36:39,695
该我们上了
We're on.

477
00:37:24,020 --> 00:37:25,931
妈妈!
Mama !

478
00:37:31,860 --> 00:37:34,135
孩子,谁要啊?
Kids.Who'd have them?

479
00:37:35,020 --> 00:37:36,419
我有四个
I've got four.

480
00:37:37,900 --> 00:37:40,937
很好,我喜欢孩子 他们跟他们母亲一样漂亮吗?
Great,I love them.They as good-looking as their mom?

481
00:37:44,420 --> 00:37:47,492
女士们,先生们,请各位就座
Ladies and gentlemen,if you could please take your seats...

